Mamelodi Sundowns have continued their shopping spree ahead of the 2018/19 season. The Brazilians have confirmed double signing of former Ajax Cape Town captain Mosa Lebusa and goalkeeper Reyaad Pieterse from SuperSport United. The duo arrives just hours before Sundowns are set to begin their Absa Premiership title defence against Soweto giants Kaizer Chiefs at the Loftus Versfeld Stadium on Saturday at 3pm.Pitso Mosimane charges have now brought in a total of seven new first team signings, including the likes of Toni Silva, Andile Jali, Lyle Lakay, Lebohang Maboe and Jose Ali Mez     